-- Russia Stocks Surge to 5-Week High as Oil, Metals Lift Producers
-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 2012-01-17T16:13:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/russia-stocks-surge-to-5-week-high-as-oil-metals-lift-producers.html
Russian stocks  climbed, lifting the
benchmark gauge to its highest level in five weeks, as rising
oil and metal prices boosted producers.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  advanced 1.5 percent to 1,486.34
by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, its highest level since Dec.
5.  OAO Severstal (CHMF) , a steelmaker, and  United Co. Rusal (RUALR) , the
world’s biggest aluminum producer, increased 3.3 percent and 4.5
percent, respectively.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH) ,  Russia ’s second-biggest oil
producer, added 1.4 percent. The dollar-denominated  RTS Index (RTSI$) 
rose 1.4 percent to 1,476.31.  Copper, aluminum and nickel gained on bets Chinese
officials will loosen monetary policy after the economy grew 8.9
percent in the fourth quarter, the slowest pace in more than two
years. Oil, Russia’s main export earner, jumped as much as 2.3
percent to $101.01 a barrel in  New York  after  Saudi Arabia  said
it wants to keep the price at $100 a barrel.  Chinese data have “given commodity prices a filip,”
Julian Rimmer, a trader of Russian shares at CF Global Trading
in  London , said by e-mail.  The Micex lost as much as 1.2 percent yesterday before
erasing its retreat to close up less than 0.1 percent after
 Standard & Poor’s  cut the credit score of  France  and eight other
countries on Jan. 13.  “Global markets seem to have digested Friday’s news about
the wave of sovereign downgrades in the EU relatively well,”
 Benoit Anne , head of global emerging markets strategy in London
at Societe Generale SA, France’s second-largest lender, said by
e-mail. “The markets backdrop seems to be turning gradually
more supportive of risky assets.”  Gazprom, TransContainer  The Micex, which has rallied 6 percent this year, trades at
5.5 times analysts’ earnings estimates for member companies, the
lowest among the so-called BRIC nations, which include  Brazil ,
India and  China .  The index dropped 17 percent in 2011, compared with an 18
percent slide for Brazil’s Bovespa index, which trades at 9.5
times estimated earnings according to data compiled by
Bloomberg. The Shanghai Composite Index trades at 9.4 times
estimated earnings, and the BSE India Sensitive Index has a
ratio of 14.4.  OAO TransContainer (TRCN)  gained 0.6 percent to 2,745.4 rubles
after the unit of OAO Russian Railways said net income in the
first nine months of last year surged to 2.96 billion rubles
($94 million) from 552 million ruble in the same period in 2010,
according to a statement released today.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP) , Russia’s gas export monopoly, said Chief
Executive Officer  Alexei Miller  and Ukraine’s Coal and Energy
Minister  Yuriy Boyko  agreed to continue talks on pricing and
transit.  The former Soviet republic is proposing reducing gas
imports by almost 50 percent, Gazprom said in a Jan. 12
statement. Gazprom rallied 1.7 percent to 181.69 rubles, its
highest level in five weeks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
